#. type: Title =
#: _guides/cyclonedx.adoc
msgid "Extension SBOM Contributions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/cyclonedx.adoc
msgid ""
"By default, Quarkus generates SBOMs from the application's Maven dependency model and the packaging output.\n"
"Extensions that manage additional software components — for example, npm packages or other non-Maven artifacts — can contribute those components to the application SBOM by producing `SbomContributionBuildItem` instances from their `@BuildStep` methods."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/cyclonedx.adoc
msgid ""
"Extension contributions are merged with the core application contribution by the SBOM generator.\n"
"Components marked as top-level will appear as direct dependencies of the main application component in the generated SBOM."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _guides/cyclonedx.adoc
msgid "API Overview"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/cyclonedx.adoc
msgid "Extension SBOM contributions are built from the following classes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/cyclonedx.adoc
msgid "`io.quarkus.sbom.Purl` — identifies a software component using the https://github.com/package-url/purl-spec[Package URL] specification. Factory methods are provided for Maven, npm, and generic component types."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/cyclonedx.adoc
msgid "`io.quarkus.sbom.ComponentDescriptor` — describes a software component with its PURL, scope, integrity hash, and other metadata."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/cyclonedx.adoc
msgid "`io.quarkus.sbom.ComponentDependencies` — describes the dependency relationships of a component, referencing other components by their bom-ref."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/cyclonedx.adoc
msgid "`io.quarkus.sbom.SbomContribution` — groups component descriptors and their dependency relationships into a single contribution."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _guides/cyclonedx.adoc
msgid "`io.quarkus.deployment.sbom.SbomContributionBuildItem` — a `MultiBuildItem` that carries an `SbomContribution` to the SBOM generator."
msgstr ""

